TY  - JOUR
T1  - Improving the Organization of Knowledge in Production by Screening Problems
AU  - Carmona, Guilherme
AU  - Laohakunakorn, Krittanai
Y1  - 2023/08/16
PY  - 2023
DA  - 2024/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/727285
DO  - 10.1086/727285
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 1290
EP  - 1326
VL  - 132
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - We extend Garicano?s model of optimal organizations by allowing problems to be screened. We show that when screening is as costly as solving problems, optimal organizations are hierarchies as in Garicano?s model, but when the cost of screening is small, workers screen all problems that they and the top managers cannot solve, those problems that they screen are sent directly to those who can solve them, and those problems that they neither solve nor screen are passed to the top managers. For intermediate values of the screening cost, the optimal organization is a hybrid of the above forms.
AB  - We extend Garicano?s model of optimal organizations by allowing problems to be screened. We show that when screening is as costly as solving problems, optimal organizations are hierarchies as in Garicano?s model, but when the cost of screening is small, workers screen all problems that they and the top managers cannot solve, those problems that they screen are sent directly to those who can solve them, and those problems that they neither solve nor screen are passed to the top managers. For intermediate values of the screening cost, the optimal organization is a hybrid of the above forms.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/727285
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/727285
Y2  - 2024/10/27
